-- Japanese Sold Net 8.9 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2012-08-01T23:58:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-01/japanese-sold-net-8-9-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended July 27 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 8.9 billion yen ($113.5 million)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 12.6 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 22 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 0.5 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 57 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 76.5 billion yen in stocks, and bought 636 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 616.6
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
